stems: is there an ideal? -- tConclusions and summary -- tIndex0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aEPUB and EPDF available Open Access under CC-BY-NC-ND licence. How do education systems shape educational inequalities and differences in educational outcomes? And how do advantages and disadvantages in educational attainment translate into privileges and shortcomings in labour market and general life chances? Education systems and inequalities compares different education systems and their impact on creating and sustaining social inequalities. The book considers key questions such as how education systems impact educational inequalities along such variables as social origin, gender, ethnicity, migration background or ability and what social mechanisms are behind the links between education system and educational inequalities and provides vital evidence to inform debates in policy and reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aComparative education. 0aDiscrimination in educationvCross-cultural studies. 0aEducation and statevCross-cultural studies. 0aEducationvCross-cultural studiesxSocial aspects. 0aEducational equalizationvCross-cultural studies. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh1 aAllmendinger, Jutta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBallarino, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Rolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernardi, Fabrizio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiermann, Jul